HEADWORD: Yalu
<hw>Ya"lu</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A river in eastern
Asia, which rises in North Korea and flows southwest to Korea Bay
(forming part of the border between North Korea and China).</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Yalu River.</syn>⟦br⟧
